				<P>I would love the Chardok B chodokai model for the 62/64 warders for iksar, but outside of that I like the fact that all pets grow (or in the case of high level necro pets change models) as the character levels.&nbsp; Its a visible measure of advancement.&nbsp; Starting them shrunk and having them enlarge via spell more or less defeats the point IMHO.&nbsp; </P>
<P>Please give an update as to the status and priority this has for the developer assigned to it.&nbsp; If necessary, allow me to suggest simply creating *new* warder models for each race if starting from scratch is easier than tracking down the bug in the code.</P>
<P>Also, for whatever its worth, I have noticed the this issue has made for other warder-type models (black wolves, shadow wolves, random tigers, etc.) to be similarly screwed up, so I suspect it is a model-related issue.&nbsp; The scaled wolves outside cabilis also appear affected.&nbsp; Interestingly enough, I have not noticed this affecting alligators or bears.&nbsp; If I were to guess, it would be that there is common underlying code governing the models for scaled wolves, wolves, and tigers.&nbsp; </P>
